The President's Weekly Address discusses the nomination of Judge Neil Gorsuch to the Supreme Court and emphasizes the importance of preserving the rule of law and democratic process in the United States. The President highlights Judge Gorsuch's qualifications and commitment to upholding the Constitution. The Address also criticizes judges who make decisions based on personal views or political opinions, stating that they undermine democracy. The Senate is called upon to confirm Judge Gorsuch, with the belief that his presence on the Supreme Court will result in a more free, fair, and just nation.